  "sourceNotes": "Carrot cake in its modern form (oil-based sponge with grated carrot and cream cheese frosting) became prominent in British baking during the 1970s, appearing in early editions of Delia Smith and then widely in Women's Institute recipe collections. Earlier versions using carrot as a sweetener appear in wartime Ministry of Food pamphlets (1940s, Crown copyright now expired). This version follows the standard post-war British pattern.",
