  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Oil-based cakes stay moist longer than butter-based ones, because oil remains liquid at room temperature while butter solidifies. This cake is better on the second day than the first: the carrot distributes its moisture evenly overnight, and the spices settle from sharp to warm. Toast the walnuts before adding them; raw walnuts in a baked cake have a bitter, papery quality that toasting removes."
          }
        ]
      },
